ss=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Majorized.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.Majorized\">Majorized</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span> <span class=\"fn\">exp</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Tendsto\">Filter.Tendsto</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/AtTopBot/Defs.html#Filter.atTop\">Filter.atTop</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Filter.html#nhds\">nhds</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `f` is majorized with a negative exponent, then it tends to zero. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Majorized.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.Majorized.tendsto_zero_of_neg","kind":"theorem","line":70,"name":"Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.Majorized.tendsto_zero_of_neg","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Majorized.lean#L70-L73"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Majorized.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.Majorized.of_le\"><span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">ComputeAsymptotics</span>.<span class=\"name\">Majorized</span>.<span class=\"name\">of_le</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">f </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">exp1 </span><spa