ml#Real\">ℝ</a> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">exp</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Tendsto\">Filter.Tendsto</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/AtTopBot/Defs.html#Filter.atTop\">Filter.atTop</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/AtTopBot/Defs.html#Filter.atTop\">Filter.atTop</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Majorized.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.Majorized\">Majorized</a> (<span class=\"fn\">f</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\">exp</span>) <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">exp</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For any function `f` tending to infinity, `f ^ exp` is majorized by `f` with exponent `exp`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Majorized.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.Majorized.self","kind":"theorem","line":46,"name":"Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.Majorized.self","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Majorized.lean#L46-L62"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Majorized.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.Majorized.of_eventuallyEq\"><span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">ComputeAsymptotics</span>.<span class=\"name\">Majorized</span>.<span class=\"name\">of_eventuallyEq</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">f </span><span class=\"fn\">g </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">exp</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h_eq</span> : <span class=\"fn\">g</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.EventuallyEq\">=ᶠ[</a><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/AtTopBot/Defs.html#Filter.atTop\">Filter.atTop</a><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.EventuallyEq\">]</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Majorized.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.Majorized\">Majorized</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span> <span class=\"fn\">exp</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Majorized.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.Majorized\">Majorized</a> <span class=\"fn\">g</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span> <span class=\"fn\">exp</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Replacing the first argument of `Majorized` by an eventually equal function preserves it. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Majorized.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.Majorized.of_eventuallyEq","kind":"theorem","line":39,"name":"Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.Majorized.of_eventuallyEq","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Majorized.lean#L39-L44"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Majorized.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.Majorized\"><span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">ComputeAsymptotics</span>.<span class=\"name\">Majorized</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a> → <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">exp</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`Majorized f g exp` for real functions `f` and `g` means that for any `exp' > exp`,\n`f =o[atTop] g ^ exp'`. This is used to define the `MultiseriesExpansion.Approximates` predicate.\nThe naming `Majorized` is non-standard because this notion is invented for the purposes of\nthis tactic, and does not exists in literature. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Majorized.html#Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.Majorized","kind":"def","line":28,"name":"Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.Majorized","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Tactic/ComputeAsymptotics/Multiseries/Majorized.lean#L28-L33"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Analysis.SpecialFunctions.Pow.Asymptotics"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.ComputeAsymptotics.Multiseries.Majorized"}